column1: # Sari procedure: I first looked for all pfams/tigrfams that had significantly different abundance among the depths. The depths were grouped together based on oxygen concentration so that the upper 5 were epilimnion
column2: then 2 metalimnion samples followed by 6 hypolimnion samples. I compared these depths using R package metagenomeSeq. Then I took all the pfams/tigrfams that were significantly different and started looking for the ones that could be used as markers of various pathways. I took proteins from pathways in metacyc and looked for the corresponding pfam/tigrfam. When I found one that was only found in the pathway in question
column3: in most cases I tested at least one of the most abundant proteins in the data that it actually is what the pram/tigrfam suggests it is. So the list should be used cautiously with other datasets.
